excerpt: Highlights from the red carpet of the Amazon Prime show "Good Omens" at the ZACH Theatre during SXSW. Stars Michael Sheen, Jon Hamm and David Tennant spoke t...
description: Michael Sheen: The story really is about this angel and this demon. A demon who’s not quite as mean and evil as he would like to think he is, and an angel who’s not quite as good as he would like to think he is. I think the more time they spend together the more they start to rub off on each other, I think that says a lot of about us. It’s our flaws and it’s our imperfections that make us who we are.

summary: Arthur “Goof” Goodall ~ Goofy ~ 37 ~ The Pier  ~ Photographer ~ FC: David Tennant                                               ...
caption:
Arthur “Goof” Goodall ~ Goofy ~ 37 ~ The Pier  ~ Photographer ~ FC: David Tennant

                                                   The Story:

Arthur saw the world differently from most. He had a slight rose-tinted-glasses perspective on the world. His parents were loving and devoted, and loved their son as much as they loved God. Raised to a pair of devout southern Christians, Arthur would go to Sunday school every week. He never minded though, he enjoyed the stories from church and all the art made him feel like he was in a art gallery. Making friends was easy for him, even if they were only friends in his eyes. Most people held a fondness for the little goof-ball, but few would consider themselves close to him.

At least until he met her. The new girl. Arthur had a tendency of befriending the new people at school, something about them being from somewhere else made him want to show them around and let them into “his world.” And for once, someone seemed to understand him too. She became his closest friend and eventually his first love. She was wild and from a troubled background, hopping from foster home to foster home. But now she was home. Or at least Arthur thought she was. When the pair were 15, she told him she was pregnant. Most kids would panic, she certainly did, but to Arthur – this was the best gift he could ever have gotten. The pregnancy was long and hard, and the town gossiped without mercy. When the time came, there were several complications and she didn’t make it. But baby Max did, and he was the most perfect thing in the world.
